gomodel:SYNGO_4566  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure S7 B,D,F show colocalization of Atg16l1 and the presynaptic marker Bassoon under normal conditions or after induction of autophagy. ATG16l1 is also found in proteomic analyses of synaptic vesicles fractions (PMID: 33376223).. Experimental description: \"Primary rat hippocampal neurons were prepared using a modified Banker culture protocol as described previously\", e3 Neuron 93, 897-913.e1-e7, February 22, 2017\n\nrabbit polyclonal anti-Atg16L from MBL; Cat# PM040Y" ;
